=Description=

"MICRONOMICS searches for creative initiatives which, through the content of their work or their way of organising, become experiments in social innovation and create new opportunities to make a living in the current economic context.

Through workshops and projects in public spaces they are brought in contact with each other, and the public is made aware of their existence.

This allows them to strengthen each others work, and clarifies their position within the economy.

Micronomics seeks to put the potential of these creative initiatives on the public agenda."
(http://micronomics.citymined.org/spip.php?rubrique5)


